# Backend Architecture (mychatAppBe)

Express + MongoDB. Request flow: **routes → controllers → services → models**.

| Layer | Responsibility | Must NOT contain |
|-------|----------------|------------------|
| `routes/` | Define endpoints, wire middleware & controller handlers | Business logic |
| `controllers/` | Parse request, call service, shape HTTP response | Business logic |
| `services/` | All business logic (brain of backend) | `req`/`res`, HTTP details |
| `models/` | Mongoose schema & structure only | Application/business logic |
| `middleware/` | Auth, validation, logging, generic cross-cutting | Business logic |
| `utils/` | Pure helpers (e.g. token generation) | Feature-specific business rules |

## Golden rules

- **Business logic never lives in routes or controllers.**
- **Services must not depend on the HTTP layer** — accept plain data, return plain data or throw errors.
- When adding features, prefer `services/<feature>Service.js` over growing controllers.

## Example (target pattern)

```javascript
// routes/users.js — endpoints only
router.get("/", protect, getUsers);

// controllers/userController.js — thin
exports.getUsers = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const users = await userService.listUsers(req.user.id);
    res.json({ success: true, data: users });
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
};

// services/userService.js — logic here
exports.listUsers = async (currentUserId) => { /* ... */ };
```

Match existing conventions: `/api/*` prefix, `{ success, data?, error? }` responses, `next(err)` for centralized errors in `server.js`.
